{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3333842,"name":"Joel Singh","username":"Joel_Singh","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joel_singh/{size}/178820_2.png","created_at":"2024-03-15T16:41:14.079Z","cooked":"

Howdy!

Our programming team doesn’t really know what the best practices towards data logging for competition. Data logging seems useful for debugging issues in the pit after matches to figure out what went wrong but we don’t really know how to go about that. Currently, we use shuffleboard and are putting a bunch of information from our subsystems to it, but not sure how to go about recording it for viewing after the match. Moreover, we saw the logging option (AdvantageScope/docs/OPEN-LIVE.md at main · Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageScope · GitHub) in advantage scope but it says it isn’t recommended for comp.

Basically we just need guidance on how we should go about logging, especially being so close to competition.

Advantage scope can also connect and view WPILOG logs. We use the inbuilt logging system (On-Robot Telemetry Recording Into Data Logs — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation) and have it log the network table data (which includes some log specific data and all of our shuffleboard data), it can also log joysticks.
Our team is relatively new to logging using this method so it might not be the best logging method but if you are already logging all the info you need to network tables you should be able to log it to a flash drive.
if you plug in a flash drive into the roborio to store the logs in make sure to check that you are able to access the logs since we had some issues with that.
You can also SFTP into the roborio and grab the logs between matches, if you let logs pile up it’ll delete the oldest logs first. (I have a vscode extension that lets me sftp into the roborio, you’ll find the logs under home/lvuser/logs or somewhere that looks like that)
I hope this helps!

Otter502:

SFTP into the roborio

The WPILib DataLogTool works well to manage the files.

The DriverStation also has the ability to fetch the log files.

We, too, had problems with incomplete or broken log files especially with a flash drive.
